honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class PrintSettings_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrintSettings_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class PrintSettings_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the Printing Settings data from an KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    BDBackup Delay
    RORow Offset
    COColumn Offset
    RFRow Adjust Fine Tune
    CFColumn Adjust Fine Tune
    PJPresent Adjust Fine Tune
    DKDarkness Level
    PCContrast Level
    HEHeatLevel
    BSBackup Speed
    SSFeed Speed
    pSPrint Speed
    FSSlew Speed
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • PrintSettings_DPL

        public PrintSettings_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
